data.title: Wimbledon 2011: Andy Murray sets up 3rd round clash with Ivan Ljubicic
data.meta_description: Andy Murray will watch more scary movies to get in the mood for a meeting with his bogeyman Ivan Ljubicic tomorrow.
data.text:
Andy Murray will watch more scary movies to get in the mood for a meeting with his bogeyman Ivan Ljubicic tomorrow.

Murray - exiled to Court One from the comfort of the Centre Court and its roof - had a fright-free passage into the third round yesterday with a straight sets win over Tobias Kamke of Germany.

But the British No.1 admitted he must raise his game against the world no.33 from Croatia.

Unlike last year, Murray, who watched horror film Scream before the victory over Kamke, was not the only Brit to win a singles match.

Elena Baltacha and Laura Robson play in the second round today.

"it doesn't change the way i go into my matches but any time British players win, it's good," added Murray.
